FBIS4-35763 "drnes107_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 LEBANON Government Reacts to Israeli Raid on Hizballah Camp Government Reacts to Israeli Raid on Hizballah Camp UN Security Council Meeting Sought NC0206113894 Paris AFP in English 1115 GMT 2 Jun 94 NC0206113894 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Beirut, June 2 (AFP)--Lebanon called for an urgent meeting of the UN Security Council after an Israeli air raid on a Hizballah training camp killed at least 45 people near the border with Syria. Defence Minister Muhsin Dallul said the decision was taken at a meeting of the Supreme Defence Council, which groups the president, prime minister, defence minister and Army chief.
